  <sect1>
    <title>Brief Installation Instructions</title>

    <para>&YP; uses a configure script as generated by <command>autoconf</command> and
      friends for configuring the build process of &YP;. Change to the
      directory where you unpacked &YPPKG; and simply type</para>

    <para>
<screen>
  <prompt>#</prompt> <literal>./configure</literal>
</screen>
    </para>

    <para>on the command line. The configure script will then check
      the system an prepares for the build process.
    </para>

    <para>If the configure script successfully finishes, type
    </para>

    <para>
<screen>
  <prompt>#</prompt> <literal>make</literal>
</screen>
    </para>

    <para>&YP; will now be builded. After the build has finished,
      switch to the root user if not done already, and type
    </para>

    <para>
<screen>
  <prompt>#</prompt> <literal>make install</literal>
</screen>
    </para>

    <para>This will install &YP; into
      the <filename>/usr/local/bin</filename> directory, if the prefix
      has not been changed by providing <option>--prefix=
	<literal>&lt;PATH&gt;</literal></option> to
      the <command>configure</command> script.</para>

</sect1>

<sect1>
  <title>Brief configure Options Description</title>

  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--prefix=</option><literal>&lt;PATH&gt;</literal>
      </term>

      <listitem>
	<para><literal>&lt;PATH&gt;</literal> is the base directory
	  where &YP; will be installed. The executable is installed in
	  <literal>&lt;PATH&gt;</literal><filename>/bin</filename>.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--with-curses-include=</option><literal>&lt;PATH&gt;</literal>
      </term>

      <listitem><para>This option tells the compiler where to find the
	header files of
	curses/ncurses. <literal>&lt;PATH&gt;</literal> has to be the
	directory where the header files are located, not the file
	name of the header file.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--with-curses-lib=</option><literal>&lt;PATH&gt;</literal>
      </term>

      <listitem>
	<para>This option tells the linker where to find the
	  curses/ncurses shared
	  library. <literal>&lt;PATH&gt;</literal> has to be the
	  directory where the shared library is located, not the file
	  name of the shared library.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--with-openssl-include=</option><literal>&lt;PATH&gt;</literal>
      </term>

      <listitem>
	<para>This options tells the compiler where to find</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--with-openssl-lib=</option><literal>&lt;PATH&gt;</literal>
      </term>

      <listitem>
	<para></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</sect1>

<sect1>
  <title>Further Information</title>

  <para>For more information about the configure script, read the
    file <filename>INSTALL.generic</filename> which comes along in the
    tarball of &YP;.</para>
</sect1>

</article>

